      <h1>What is Seam Carving?</h1>
      <h1>
        Seam carving is a way to resize images by automatically removing or adding pixels in the least noticeable areas. It works by finding the least important pixel paths (seams) across the image and deleting or inserting pixels along those seams. This allows the image to be made smaller or larger while keeping the important objects and details intact.
